Stream; and the beauty secrets of ancient Amazons. Other pieces examine Arthur Conan Doyle’s sea serpent and Geronimo’s dragon; Flaubert’s obsession with ancient Carthage; ancient tattooing practices; and the strange relationship between wine goblets and women’s breasts since the times of Helen of Troy and Marie Antoinette. And there’s much, much more.Showcasing Mayor’s trademark passion not to demythologize myths, but to uncover the fascinating truths buried beneath them, Flying Snakes and Griffin Claws is a wonder cabinet of delightful curiosities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCuriosities and wonders. 0aFolklore. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aAdrienne Mayor.  aAmazons.  aAncient Greek literature.  aAncient Greek.  aAncient history.  aAncient literature.  aAncient warfare.  aAnecdote.  aArchaeology.  aAristeas.  aAthens.  aAuthor.  aBeak.  aBiological warfare.  aBrooch.  aCartography.  aCertainty.  aChapter 33 (G.I. Bill of Rights).  aClassical mythology.  aClassics.  aCross-reference.  aCryptid.  aCryptozoology.  aCurator.  aDinosaur egg.  aDog food.  aDrawing.  aEnglish language.  aEssay.  aFairy.  aFirst Book.  aFolklore.  aFranz Kafka.  aGoatherd.  aGriffin.  aGustave Flaubert.  aHerodotus.  aIllustration.  aJosiah Ober.  aLatin literature.  aLegendary creature.  aLibation.  aLibrary stack.  aLiterature.  aLondon Review of Books.  aLow culture.  aMagazine.  aManuscript.  aMartyr.  aMemoir.  aMilitary history.  aMiscellany.  aMuseum of the Rockies.  aMythology.  aOrigin story.  aPaleontology.  aPopular Science.  aPopular culture.  aPopular science.  aPottery.  aPrintmaking.  aPublication.  aQuadrupedalism.  aRevised Version.  aSaronic Gulf.  aSatyr.  aScientist.  